cz.muni.fi.virtualtoolmanager.pubapi.managers

Interface ConnectionManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConnectionManagerImpl

    public interface ConnectionManager
    Interface that declare what method the implementation of the connection manager should provide.
    By implementing the declared methods, it should be possible to remotely access a particular physical machine with the virtualization tool VirtualBox.
    See Also:
    ConnectionManagerImpl, ClosingActionType

    • Method Detail

      • connectTo

        VirtualizationToolManager connectTo(PhysicalMachine physicalMachine)
        Method that ensures the connection establishment with the required physical machine on which is present the VirtualBox installation with the web server that must be running at the moment when there is made an attempt to establish the connection with the physical machine.

        The physical machine with which should be the connection established is defined by input parameter of type PhysicalMachine.

        If the physical machine is connected successfully, then as the result of the connection operation is returned an object of type VirtualizationToolManager and the operations with the newly accessible virtual machines can be performed.

        The connected physical machine is connected until any disconnection operation is called for that physical machine.

        Parameters:
        physicalMachine - represents host machine which is going to get connected
        Returns:
        manager of type VirtualizationToolManager for managing virtual machines on the newly connected physical machine

      • connectTo

        VirtualizationToolManager connectTo(PhysicalMachine physicalMachine,
                                    long millis)
        Method that is same as connectTo(PhysicalMachine), but with this method is possible to define the time in milliseconds which determine the waiting time between each unsuccessful connection establishment attempt.
        Parameters:
        physicalMachine - represents host machine which is going to get connected
        millis - time in milliseconds determining the waiting time between each unsuccessful connection establishment attempt
        Returns:
        manager of type VirtualizationToolManager for managing virtual machines on the newly connected physical machine

      • disconnectFrom

        void disconnectFrom(PhysicalMachine physicalMachine)
        Method that ensures the disconnection of a particular physical machine.

        After the method call there cannot be performed any operation with virtual machines from the disconnected physical machine.

        Parameters:
        physicalMachine - represents the host machine which is going to be disconnected

      • disconnectFrom

        void disconnectFrom(PhysicalMachine physicalMachine,
                    ClosingActionType closingAction)
        Method that is same as disconnectFrom(PhysicalMachine), but furthermore there can be specified if and what final actions shall be performed during the physical machine disconnection operation.
        Parameters:
        physicalMachine - represents the host machine which is going to be disconnected
        closingAction - represents the final action which should be performed during the disconnection operation

      • isConnected

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if the queried physical machine is connected, false otherwise
